    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>The Detroit News Lansing Bureau was responsible for reporting news of Michigan government and politics, including the activities of the governor and the workings of the legislature.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The records consists primarily of scrapbooks dating from 1931 to 1966, miscellaneous press and reference files, and clippings of articles by reporter Glenn Engle. The scrapbooks provide detailed and complete coverage of state government with particular emphasis on the gubernatorial administrations of Kim Sigler, G. Mennen Williams, John Swainson and George Romney. There are also clippings pertaining to Michigan politics, the work of Michigan's Grand Jury (1943-1962), and the state constitutional convention, 1961-1964.</p>
    </scopecontent>
